  "name": "Coronary Heart Disease - Secondary Prevention Medication Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find CHD patients via secondary prevention medications. Standard CHD secondary prevention includes: aspirin (antiplatelet), clopidogrel (P2Y12 inhibitor — DAPT after PCI), statins (atorvastatin, simvastatin), and beta blockers (carvedilol post-MI). All have heavy cross-indication use. The Synthea module distributes patients across these classes.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed secondary prevention medications used after coronary heart disease, including aspirin, clopidogrel, statins like atorvastatin or simvastatin, and beta blockers like carvedilol.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on heart attack prevention medications.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed secondary prevention medications used after coronary heart disease — antiplatelet agents (aspirin, clopidogrel), high-intensity statins (atorvastatin, simvastatin), and beta blockers (carvedilol).",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any CHD secondary prevention drug. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 1191 (aspirin, antiplatelet), 32968 (clopidogrel, P2Y12 inhibitor), 83367 (atorvastatin, statin), 36567 (simvastatin, statin), 20352 (carvedilol, beta blocker post-MI). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Note all five have heavy cross-indication use — aspirin for primary prevention, statins for general lipid management, carvedilol for HF/HTN."
  },
